UML:TaggedValue.value: This will submit a task to the external analysis tool and the return of execute is a String of the Task id that is being run.
This service is what will convert our raw data into data that is readable by any external analysis tools such as Gene Pattern.

When loading data, the user gives a source (such as NCIA, CTODs, or a Local File), type such as Clinical, Genomic, Imaging, a key column which is what will map the AnnotationValues to their proper subjects
Takes in a logical data table, and a Map of Original Column Name -> AnnotationDefinition and writes the data to the AnnotationDefinition and AnnotationValue classes
This is a high level data loader that loads a "table" from a datasource and converts it to our annotation definition / annotation value pair tables.

Overloaded bean that will contain the different types of data sources we can use for loading in data. You must set the sourceType and then if it's a "file" type the file will be set, if it's a grid type the gridConnectionString will be set.
A LogicalDataTable is the data type that we are using to store the incoming data from a data source which will be converted to the AnnotationDefinition and AnnotationValue paradigm.
